Package org.variantsync.diffdetective.diff.difftree.parse

Record Class ParseResult

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Record
org.variantsync.diffdetective.diff.difftree.parse.ParseResult
Record Components:
type - Decides if an element was parsed successfully or not .
errorType - An error description in case an error occurred.
message - A custom message.
public record ParseResult(ParseResultType type, DiffError errorType, String message) extends Record
Result type for parsing. Mostly used for parsing multiline macros.
Author:
Paul Bittner

  • Field Details

    • SUCCESS

      public static final ParseResult SUCCESS
      Default value for returning that parsing was successful.

    • NOT_MY_DUTY

      public static final ParseResult NOT_MY_DUTY
      Default value for returning that a token was not parsed because it was not relevant for a certain parser. This is mostly used by the MultiLineMacroParser when it finds a source code line that is not part of a multiline macro definition.
